            1,& x \ne 2; \\\\
            3, & x = 2.
        \end{cases}
    What is its value as $x \to 2$?
    \source{Чему равняется её предел при $x \to 2$?}

    You nay be tempted to just evaluate the function at $x=2$ and conclude that the answer is $3$.
    However, this is incorrect.
    In fact, the value of a function in $x=2$ does not affect the limit at all!
    The actual values that determine the answer are the values in points near $x_0$.
    \source
